article.headline: Scarlet Knights notch eighth consecutive win
article.linkText: Pondexter paces Rutgers in win over St. John's
article.story:
NEW YORK (AP) -- Cappie Pondexter had 21 points, nine rebounds and seven assists as Rutgers (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today; No. 22 AP) extended its winning streak to eight games with a 69-38 victory Wednesday night over St. John's.

	   The Scarlet Knights have won 10 straight over the Red Storm and
hold a 25-3 advantage in the series. Rutgers last lost to St.
John's on Jan. 30, 1996.

	   Chelsea Newton had 14 points for Rutgers (17-5, 10-2 Big East),
which held a 29-19 lead at halftime. Courtney Locke added 10.

	   Reka Szavuly, who made four of eight from 3-point range, topped
the Red Storm (8-16, 2-11) with 18 points. Shemika Stevens had 11
points for St. John's, which lost its fourth straight.

	   A jumper by Patrycja Gulak lifted St. John's into an 11-11 tie
midway through the first half. But Pondexter made two 3-pointers in
a 14-4 run as Rutgers took a 25-15 lead 3:58 before the break. Two
free throws by Newton closed the run.

	   Szavuly's basket got St. John's within 36-30 with 13:37
remaining in the game. The Rutgers defense then held the Red Storm
to eight points the rest of the way, while the offense scored 33
behind Locke's 10 and Pondexter's nine.
